## "description" model
The common model for a descriptive value and associated properties.

| Property | Definition | Value type | Repeatable |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| value | String value of the descriptive element. | String | No |
| code | Code value of the descriptive element. | String | No |
| type | Type of value provided by the descriptive element. | String | No |
| status | Status of the descriptive element value relative to other instances. | String | No |
| uri | URI value of the descriptive element. | String | No |
| standard | Descriptive or content standard to which the value conforms. | Object ("standard" model) | No |
| encoding | Encoding schema, standard, or syntax to which the value conforms. | Object ("encoding" model) | No |
| identifier | Identifiers and URIs associated with the descriptive element. Identifier types must be from the "identifier" controlled list. | Object ("description" model) | Yes |
| source | The vocabulary, authority, or other origin for a term, code, or identifier. | Object ("source" model) | No |
| displayLabel | The preferred display label to use for the descriptive element in access systems. | String | No |
| qualifier | A term providing information about the circumstances of the statement (e.g., approximate dates). | String | No |
| note | Other information related to the descriptive element. Note types must be from the "note" controlled list unless a different controlled list is specified in other instructions. | Object ("description" model) | Yes |
| valueLanguage | Language of the descriptive element value. | Object ("value language" model) | No |
| valueAt | URL or other pointer to the location of the value of the descriptive element. | String | No |
| structuredValue | Multiple values intended to be concatenated in order to form a single value. | Object ("description" model) | Yes |
| parallelValue | Multiple representations of the same information, such as in different languages. | Object ("description" model) | Yes |
| groupedValue | For interoperability with MODS. | Object ("description" model) | Yes |
| appliesTo | Portion or aspect of the resource the value applies to. | Object ("description" model) | Yes |

## "standard" model
| Property | Definition | Value type | Repeatable |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| value | String describing the standard. | String | No |
| code | Code representing the standard. | String | No |
| uri | URI for the standard. | String | No |
| note | Other information related to the standard. Note types must be from the "note" controlled list. | Object ("description" model) | Yes |
| source | The vocabulary, authority, or other origin for the standard. | Object ("source" model) | No |
| version | The version of the standard. | String | No |

